issues.title: Plugin references don't match Facebook
issues.body: The plugin references "Consumer Key" and "Consumer Secret", when Facebook uses "App ID" and "App Secret" as the labels

issues.title: Provide error message when no apps are set up
issues.body: Attempting to add a Connected Account for Facebook Pages, prior to configuring a facebook app, results in an odd error condition (a blank new window opens).  We should perhaps disable the [Facebook Pages] button in the Add Connected Account popup, or more optimally provide an informational message explaining what they need to do first.

issues.title: Ability to post to Facebook pages instead of just profiles

commit.message: * [Plugins/Facebook] Implemented the Facebook Pages service provider for connected accounts.
* [Plugins/Facebook] Implemented the Facebook service provider for connected accounts.
* [Plugins/Facebook/OAuth] Removed the 'oauth' PHP extension requirement in the Facebook plugin. The plugin now also works when an proxy is configured for outgoing requests.
[OAuth] Use the cURL engine rather than fsockopen
* [Plugins/Facebook] Fixed an issue with Facebook API permission names changing.
Implemented elastic text area in VA action.  Added a warning when a Facebook account isn't configured.
Added Virtual Attendant behavior + macro variable support
Added the ability to remove Facebook accounts
